file=Cybersecurity/warden/custom/risk-register/assets/risk-register-template.md · rr—:Risk Register — [business name]=> Append-only. Every risk: asset × threat × vuln, scored (risk_score.py), treated, owned. Acceptance above `risk_acceptance_threshold` → board. Scales are operator-set (rule 0.5), flagged reasoning-based (0.6) until the risk-management source.\n · tb=\| ID \| Asset \| Threat \| Vulnerability \| Likelihood \| Impact \| Score \| Crown-jewel \| Treatment \| Owner \| Review \| Status \| · tb=\|---\|---\|---\|---\|---\|---\|---\|---\|---\|---\|---\|---\| · tb=\| R-001 \| <FILL_IN> \| \| \| [1-5] \| [1-5] \| [L×I] \| y/n \| mitigate/transfer/avoid/ACCEPT \| \| [date] \| open/treated/accepted-by-X-on-date \| · tb=\| Risk ID \| Accepted by \| Date \| Rationale \| Board ref (if above threshold) \| Review-by \| · tb=\|---\|---\|---\|---\|---\|---\| · c:Config=- likelihood_scale / impact_scale: <FILL_IN> (default 5×5)\n- risk_acceptance_threshold: <FILL_IN> (above → board; e.g. score ≥ 15)\n- crown_jewel_assets: <FILL_IN> (weight up)\n- review_cadence: <FILL_IN>\n